      "prompt": "Daily memory compression routine.\n\n1. Run `wc -c $HERMES_HOME/memories/MEMORY.md` and `wc -c $HERMES_HOME/memories/USER.md` via terminal.\n2. Read `$HERMES_HOME/config.yaml` and extract `memory.memory_char_limit` (default 2200) and `memory.user_char_limit` (default 2000).\n3. Calculate usage percentage for each file.\n4. If BOTH are below 80%, respond with exactly \"[SILENT]\" and nothing else.\n5. If either is 80% or above:\n   - Read the target file(s) with read_file.\n   - Identify verbose entries: long-winded phrasing, redundant words, mergeable duplicate facts. Do NOT delete factual content.\n   - Compress each entry by shortening wording while keeping all facts intact.\n   - Apply each change with `memory(action='replace', target='memory' or 'user', old_string='...', new_string='...')`.\n   - If a replace fails because old_string no longer matches, skip it and continue.\n   - Report final usage percentages and a brief summary of what was compressed.\n\nImportant: Only compress when usage is \u226580%. Preserve all environment facts, paths, and critical constraints.",
